@skullriot

Have you ever considered that maybe you just have a crappy player and your codecs suck? 53 sounds just like the rest when I watch it. So maybe rather than instantly saying it's the file, try updating whatever crap you're using and listen again.

To recap, pay no mind to the comment about the audio being off. Get all the most recent codecs, and update your players, then try to play it and it should work fine. I run this in Media Player Classic HC and it works exactly how it should.

@skullriot @phat_71

or it could be you're running too many cpu-intensive apps at the same time. i've experienced many a skipped frame / distorted audio just simply because i was unzipping a 4GB file (algorithm + disk access = CPU INTENSE).

if changing codecs doesn't help, try making sure your com isn't overburdened.
